name: Embedded Multicore Building Blocks (EMB²)
description: C/C++ library for parallel programming of embedded systems
description_good_justification: Besides a description of the key features and a simple example for using the library, the website also provides background information and lists frequently asked questions.
interact_justification: The website contains general information about how to contact the community: https://embb.io/keep_in_touch.html. Additional information can be found in https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/README.md and https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md.
contribution_justification: Detailed information on the contribution process is given in https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md.
contribution_requirements_justification: Besides process-related information, https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md describes the coding guidelines (incl. tool support such as cpplint and cppcheck) as well as guidelines for documenting the code.
license_location_justification: The license file COPYING.md is contained in the root folder of the project: https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/COPYING.md.
floss_license_justification: The BSD licenses (2-clause and 3-clause) meet the above requirements (see also https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/COPYING.md). The BSD-2-Clause license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
floss_license_osi_justification: Both, BSD 2-clause and 3-clause are approved by OSI (https://opensource.org/licenses/alphabetical). The BSD-2-Clause license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: Installation instructions are given in https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/README.md. The release files contain a tutorial explaining the basics (including examples).
documentation_interface_justification: The reference manual, which is part of the release files, describes the APIs (Doxygen documentation).
repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public Git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_interim_justification: All changes, bug fixes, new features, etc. are published on GitHub (in separate branches) for review.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_tags_justification: For each version, there is a corresponding Git tag.
release_notes_vulns_justification: For each release, CHANGELOG.md contains a section on known bugs.
report_tracker_justification: Issues are tracked using GitHub: https://github.com/siemens/embb/issues
report_process_justification: Bug reports can be submitted via GitHub (https://github.com/siemens/embb/issues) using the 'bug' label.
report_responses_justification: The majority of bugs is fixed with high priority (see, for example, https://github.com/siemens/embb/issues?q=label%3Abug).
enhancement_responses_justification: We try to address enhancements as soon as possible (see, for example, https://github.com/siemens/embb/issues?q=label%3Aenhancement).
report_archive_justification: GitHub's issue tracker allows to search for open and already closed issues: https://github.com/siemens/embb/issues
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: See section "Contributing" in https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md or the FAQ (https://embb.io/faq.html).
vulnerability_report_private_justificati: Private vulnerability reports can be sent via mail to embb.info@gmail.com (see also https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md or https://embb.io/faq.html).
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: No vulnerability reports received so far.
build_common_tools_justification: EMB² is built using CMake, which is commonly used on a variety of platforms.
build_floss_tools_justification: As described in https://github.com/siemens/embb/blob/master/README.md, CMake and GCC are sufficient to build the project.
test_justification: The unit tests and scripts shipped with the project have the same license (BSD 2-clause).
test_invocation_justification: After building the project, the test suite can be started by typing 'binaries/run_tests.sh' (or 'binaries\run_tests.bat' on Windows).
test_most_justification: At the time of this writing, statement coverage is 91%.
tests_are_added_justification: Tests are part of code reviews which are carried out before new functionality is merged into the development branch. Moreover, test coverage is regularly tracked via CI.
warnings_justification: The default warning flag is '-Wall'. Additionally, we employ cpplint and cppcheck to detect code quality errors.
warnings_fixed_justification: To enforce our zero warnings policy, nightly builds are executed such that warnings are treated as errors. Hence, release builds are guaranteed to be warning-free for the supported compiler versions.
delivery_mitm_justification: GitHub uses https for downloading release files: https://github.com/siemens/embb/releases
delivery_unsigned_justification: Vacuously true since no hashes are transferred.
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: No vulnerabilities known, bugs are fixed with high priority.
vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: No vulnerabilities known, bugs are fixed with high priority.
static_analysis_justification: We use Coverity Scan (https://scan.coverity.com/projects/siemens-embb) and cppcheck (see below) for static analysis.
static_analysis_often_justification: cppcheck is run by our internal CI server (Jenkins) on every commit and breaks the build in case of any warnings. Additionally, we regularly run Coverity Scan (https://scan.coverity.com/projects/siemens-embb).
dynamic_analysis_justification: We use Helgrind to detect concurrency issues such as data races and a linearizability checker to verify the data structures provided by the library.
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: Since version 0.5.0 we run Microsoft's AppVerifier before major releases, e.g. to detect memory safety problems.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: Invariants and assumptions are checked using assertions. Values that depend on the environment (e.g., user input) are always checked, not only in debug mode as in case of assertions.
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: So far, we didn't encounter any severe vulnerabilities, but generally fix bugs in a timely way.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: Jenkins is used to build the project at every push. Additionally, Jenkins also runs tests and various tools for static/dynamic analysis on a nightly basis.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
no_leaked_credentials_justification: The repository does not contain any credentials.
english_justification: All documentation as well as GitHub issues are in English.
crypto_used_network_justification: EMB² provides a plugin for the MTAPI scheduler that permits communication between multiple nodes via sockets. The plugin may be used for communication in isolated environments (e.g., heterogeneous systems with distributed memory) and serves as an example for the implementation of custom plugins. It is not meant to be used for large clusters or communication via the Internet. The plugin is disabled by default and must be initialized explicitly by the user before using it.
hardened_site_justification: X-Content-Type-Options was not set to "nosniff".
installation_common_justification: Installation is pretty easy as described in the README file. To uninstall the project, only the folder containing the library has to be deleted.

https://github.com/yeriomin/YalpStore
https://f-droid.org/repository/browse/?fdid=com.github.yeriomin.yalpstore

Every release has a brief summary of issues fixed and features implemented in this release.

Both project github page and the app itself have a disclaimer/warning that using this app with live Google account is unsafe due to Google ToS violation.
https://github.com/yeriomin/YalpStore/blob/master/README.md
report_responses_justification:
Most issues have both a text answer from the dev and a linked commit.
Issues list showing least recently updated issues first:

build_justification:
F-droid builds every release automatically.
https://f-droid.org/wiki/page/com.github.yeriomin.yalpstore
Travis-ci is used to build and attach release apks to github releases.
https://travis-ci.org/yeriomin/YalpStore
Gradle is used to build the project, every developer who clones the github repo can build it from scratch by starting the gradle build task.
https://github.com/yeriomin/YalpStore/blob/master/app/build.gradle
build_common_tools_justification:

https://github.com/yeriomin/YalpStore/blob/master/app/build.gradle
crypto_published_justification: Yalp Store works with Google servers, which use TLS 1.3
crypto_call_justification: NetCipher is used to initiate https connections
crypto_floss_justification: TLS implementation of the Android OS is used, which is open source.
crypto_keylength_justification: This is not Yalp Store's choice. The choice depends on the software used on Google servers.

no_leaked_credentials_justification: Credentials are not stored in code.
hardened_site_justification: Found all required security hardening headers.

* f-droid https://f-droid.org/repository/browse/?fdid=com.github.yeriomin.yalpstore
* github releases https://github.com/yeriomin/YalpStore/releases
